<li id="cite_note-JVIL2006-1">^ <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-5" title=""><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-6" title=""><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-7" title=""><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-8" title=""><sup><i><b>i</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-9" title=""><sup><i><b>j</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-10" title=""><sup><i><b>k</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-11" title=""><sup><i><b>l</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-12" title=""><sup><i><b>m</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-13" title=""><sup><i><b>n</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-14" title=""><sup><i><b>o</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-15" title=""><sup><i><b>p</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-16" title=""><sup><i><b>q</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-17" title=""><sup><i><b>r</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-18" title=""><sup><i><b>s</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-19" title=""><sup><i><b>t</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-20" title=""><sup><i><b>u</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-21" title=""><sup><i><b>v</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-22" title=""><sup><i><b>w</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-23" title=""><sup><i><b>x</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-24" title=""><sup><i><b>y</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-25" title=""><sup><i><b>z</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-26" title=""><sup><i><b>aa</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-27" title=""><sup><i><b>ab</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JVIL2006_1-28" title=""><sup><i><b>ac</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/jewpop.html" class="external text" title="http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/jewpop.html" rel="nofollow">"The Jewish Population of the World (2006)"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Jewish_Virtual_Library" title="Jewish Virtual Library">Jewish Virtual Library</a></i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/jewpop.html" class="external free" title="http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/jewpop.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/jewpop.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+Jewish+Population+of+the+World+%282006%29&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BJewish+Virtual+Library%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jewishvirtuallibrary.org%2Fjsource%2FJudaism%2Fjewpop.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Jew"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>, based on <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book"><i><a href="http://www.ajcarchives.org/main.php?GroupingId=10142" class="external text" title="http://www.ajcarchives.org/main.php?GroupingId=10142" rel="nofollow">American Jewish Year Book</a></i>. <b>106</b>. <a href="/wiki/American_Jewish_Committee" title="American Jewish Committee">American Jewish Committee</a>. 2006<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.ajcarchives.org/main.php?GroupingId=10142" class="external free" title="http://www.ajcarchives.org/main.php?GroupingId=10142" rel="nofollow">http://www.ajcarchives.org/main.php?GroupingId=10142</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=American+Jewish+Year+Book&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.volume=106&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BAmerican+Jewish+Committee%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ajcarchives.org%2Fmain.php%3FGroupingId%3D10142&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Jew"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> According to the <a href="/wiki/The_American_Heritage_Dictionary_of_the_English_Language" title="The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language">The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language</a>, Fourth Edition (2000): "It is widely recognized that the attributive use of the noun <i>Jew</i>, in phrases such as <i>Jew lawyer</i> or <i>Jew ethics</i>, is both vulgar and highly offensive. In such contexts <i>Jewish</i> is the only acceptable possibility. Some people, however, have become so wary of this construction that they have extended the stigma to any use of <i>Jew</i> as a noun, a practice that carries risks of its own. In a sentence such as <i>There are now several Jews on the council</i>, which is unobjectionable, the substitution of a circumlocution like <i>Jewish people</i> or <i>persons of Jewish background</i> may in itself cause offense for seeming to imply that Jew has a negative connotation when used as a noun. <a href="http://www.bartleby.com/61/75/J0037500.html" class="external text" title="http://www.bartleby.com/61/75/J0037500.html" rel="nofollow">"Jew"</a>, <a href="/wiki/The_American_Heritage_Dictionary_of_the_English_Language" title="The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language">The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language</a>, Fourth Edition (2000).</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> Johnson (1987), p. 82.</li>
